cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CS Paper Roadmaps: Curated Reading Lists for Computer Science"
message: "If you reference this resource in academic work, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - name: "CS Paper Roadmaps Contributors"
    website: "https://github.com/Achal13jain/cs-paper-roadmaps"
abstract: >-
  Eleven curated, logically ordered reading paths through the foundational
  and frontier papers of modern computing — sequenced so each builds on the
  last, with TL;DRs, prerequisites, and key takeaways. Covers LLMs,
  Computer Vision, Reinforcement Learning, Distributed Systems, Graph Neural
  Networks, Database Systems, Cryptography, Information Retrieval, Computer
  Architecture, Computational Biology, and Programming Languages.
  258 papers across 11 fields, spanning 1936 – 2024.
keywords:
  - reading-list
  - computer-science
  - machine-learning
  - paper-curation
  - bibliography
  - research-roadmap
